txt.en: You have discovered Eilendoth perched above the Ringló Vale. It is kept by Authest, ever steadfast in his duty.

The village of Ethring stands on either side of the main fords of the Ringló. After dealing with the Ruthless Dead, spiders, and Orcs during the Dawnless Day, its denizens are eager for a return to normalcy.
You have discovered the lumber camp
During the Dawnless Day, Dâr Matum played host to the Ruthless Dead under Drugât's command. In their absence, a brood of spiders has taken roost.
The lumber camp lies upriver from Ethring. Its products will be vital to the restoration of Gondor.
You have discovered Gríshru, a White Mountain Orc camp.
The so-called 'Bolt-holes' is the last remaining refuge for brigands in the Vale.
Explore the Ringló Vale in western King's Gondor.
